00:16:07,620 --> 00:16:10,300
It's all because he's an older brother.
That's why he acts that way.

280
00:16:10,960 --> 00:16:11,960
So that's it.

281
00:16:12,160 --> 00:16:13,430
So that's what this is about.

282
00:16:14,680 --> 00:16:16,220
Hey! What's your problem?

283
00:16:17,440 --> 00:16:18,440
Nothing.

284
00:16:18,560 --> 00:16:19,790
It's none of your business.

285
00:16:20,910 --> 00:16:21,910
What about you?

286
00:16:21,950 --> 00:16:23,419
Don't you have any?

287
00:16:23,420 --> 00:16:24,090
Siblings?

288
00:16:24,120 --> 00:16:25,830
Oh, yeah! Two older sisters.

289
00:16:26,890 --> 00:16:28,030
Oh...

290
00:16:28,560 --> 00:16:29,560
That explains it.

291
00:16:30,320 --> 00:16:30,870
Huh?
What?

292
00:16:32,620 --> 00:16:33,620
Nothing.

293
00:16:33,700 --> 00:16:34,700
It's nothing.

294
00:16:35,260 --> 00:16:36,420
None of your business.

295
00:16:36,770 --> 00:16:37,770
What's your deal?

296
00:16:42,470 --> 00:16:43,476
Man, time is flying, isn't it?

297
00:16:43,500 --> 00:16:44,500
The trip ends tomorrow.

298
00:16:45,150 --> 00:16:46,150
I know, right?

299
00:16:46,310 --> 00:16:48,230
It feels like it went by
in the blink of an eye.

300
00:16:48,740 --> 00:16:49,740
Yeah, you're right.

301
00:16:50,350 --> 00:16:51,640
The school trip.

302
00:16:51,760 --> 00:16:52,980
It ends tomorrow.

303
00:16:53,590 --> 00:16:55,800
But summer break is coming up.

304
00:16:57,350 --> 00:17:00,140
Right! We said we'd all
go to the beach this year.

305
00:17:00,490 --> 00:17:01,490
And do fireworks, too.

306
00:17:02,330 --> 00:17:03,330
It's kinda crazy...

307
00:17:03,960 --> 00:17:05,760
I was so nervous at first.

308
00:17:05,990 --> 00:17:06,990
Oh.

309
00:17:07,020 --> 00:17:09,086
Hey, we should come back
to an amusement park again.

310
00:17:09,110 --> 00:17:10,110
Totally!

311
00:17:10,320 --> 00:17:11,620
Let's all go again.

312
00:17:12,070 --> 00:17:12,500
Yeah, let's.

313
00:17:12,510 --> 00:17:16,070
Hioki, you'll have to get over
your fear of roller coasters first.

314
00:17:16,200 --> 00:17:18,200
Huh... you think I can?

315
00:17:19,170 --> 00:17:21,120
And you have to try the
haunted house again.

316
00:17:21,970 --> 00:17:22,970
No... that's a hard pass.

317
00:17:23,960 --> 00:17:24,960
Without realizing it,

318
00:17:25,660 --> 00:17:28,500
we've gotten to a point where we
can just look at each other and smile.

319
00:17:35,560 --> 00:17:37,306
There's no way I can
be satisfied with just this.

320
00:17:37,330 --> 00:17:39,800
Tomorrow, I have to...

321
00:17:43,810 --> 00:17:47,380
- Okay, let's check in.
- I'm so excited.

322
00:17:48,320 --> 00:17:50,710
On the second day, we moved to a hotel...

323
00:17:50,760 --> 00:17:52,880
Actually, there was a bit of a mix-up.

324
00:17:53,170 --> 00:17:55,619
I'm so sorry... about your rooms.

325
00:17:55,620 --> 00:17:59,700
There aren't enough beds. So... I'm
hoping you can all work something out.

326
00:18:01,980 --> 00:18:03,020
Mr. Kokufu.

327
00:18:03,850 --> 00:18:04,890
Yes, of course.

328
00:18:05,210 --> 00:18:06,290
Yes, no problem.

329
00:18:06,520 --> 00:18:07,530
Yes, it's fine.

330
00:18:07,660 --> 00:18:10,220
- No problem at all. We've got it covered.
- Miss...

331
00:18:10,500 --> 00:18:11,820
- Not a problem.
- But...

332
00:18:12,020 --> 00:18:13,890
Yes, of course.

333
00:18:17,130 --> 00:18:18,880
- How does this even happen?
- Seriously?

334
00:18:21,250 --> 00:18:22,650
So, who's sharing with who?

335
00:18:23,040 --> 00:18:24,960
I toss and turn a lot, so I'm out.

336
00:18:25,060 --> 00:18:26,410
- Same here.
- What?

337
00:18:28,560 --> 00:18:29,560
So...

338
00:18:29,730 --> 00:18:31,690
How about it, should we
play rock-paper-scissors?

339
00:18:35,660 --> 00:18:37,880
Actually, considering our heights,

340
00:18:38,020 --> 00:18:40,340
wouldn't it be too cramped
for Watarai and Hotta to share?

341
00:18:40,420 --> 00:18:41,640
Good point.

342
00:18:41,940 --> 00:18:43,850
With two people in that bed...

343
00:18:44,100 --> 00:18:45,130
It'd be...

344
00:18:45,490 --> 00:18:46,490
So...

345
00:18:47,150 --> 00:18:48,340
Um...

346
00:18:48,490 --> 00:18:50,566
Why don't the pairs who sat
together on the bus just share?

347
00:18:50,590 --> 00:18:51,590
Huh?

348
00:18:54,080 --> 00:18:55,280
I mean, I'm...

349
00:18:55,380 --> 00:18:56,580
I'm cool with it.

350
00:18:56,750 --> 00:18:57,949
He actually agreed.

351
00:18:57,950 --> 00:19:00,170
Oh, but it's up to Hioki.

352
00:19:00,760 --> 00:19:02,330
Huh? Oh, uh...

353
00:19:02,620 --> 00:19:03,620
I... I'm okay with it.

354
00:19:04,920 --> 00:19:05,920
Seriously?

355
00:19:06,120 --> 00:19:07,120
You sure?

356
00:19:08,100 --> 00:19:09,100
Awesome!

357
00:19:09,380 --> 00:19:11,310
Which bed?

358
00:19:11,890 --> 00:19:12,890
I'll take this one.

359
00:19:14,340 --> 00:19:15,890
Aww, then I'll take that one.

360
00:19:16,340 --> 00:19:17,340
I'll take this bed.

361
00:19:18,360 --> 00:19:19,360
For real?

362
00:19:19,890 --> 00:19:21,540
Well... here we go, I guess.

363
00:19:22,420 --> 00:19:23,420
Yeah.

364
00:19:28,500 --> 00:19:31,650
We decided that pretty quickly, but...

365
00:20:01,950 --> 00:20:02,950
it feels like...

366
00:20:03,810 --> 00:20:06,260
this is a lot closer than I thought.

367
00:20:13,210 --> 00:20:15,119
But we're both guys anyway,

368
00:20:15,120 --> 00:20:17,770
so it shouldn't be a big deal.

369
00:20:22,720 --> 00:20:24,880
You're gonna fall off
sleeping that close to the edge.

370
00:20:25,860 --> 00:20:26,860
Yeah.

371
00:20:27,900 --> 00:20:28,900
You're... right.

372
00:20:31,240 --> 00:20:33,530
Even so, this is way too close, isn't it?

373
00:20:34,110 --> 00:20:34,820
What is with him?

374
00:20:34,821 --> 00:20:37,301
Do all good-looking guys have a
weird sense of personal space?

375
00:20:37,350 --> 00:20:38,570
Ugh, seriously.

376
00:20:39,570 --> 00:20:40,920
I'm too nervous to sleep.

377
00:21:01,160 --> 00:21:02,360
Back then...

378
00:21:03,270 --> 00:21:04,470
Watarai...

379
00:21:05,510 --> 00:21:06,710
What do you...

380
00:21:08,530 --> 00:21:09,730
like about me?

381
00:21:12,110 --> 00:21:15,860
I have no idea what the
right answer would have been.

382
00:21:16,910 --> 00:21:17,910
But...

383
00:21:18,900 --> 00:21:19,900
by the way,

384
00:21:21,350 --> 00:21:22,910
why are you so protective of Hioki-kun?

385
00:21:26,910 --> 00:21:27,910
Huh?

386
00:21:29,680 --> 00:21:31,810
You guys weren't even
that close at the beginning.

387
00:21:37,490 --> 00:21:38,590
Watarai-kun.

388
00:21:40,460 --> 00:21:41,660
Hioki-kun...

389
00:21:42,830 --> 00:21:44,110
What's so good about him anyway?

390
00:21:49,750 --> 00:21:51,510
Hmm... how should I put it?

391
00:21:54,310 --> 00:21:55,510
Everything about him.

392
00:22:00,360 --> 00:22:01,360
But for now,

393
00:22:03,400 --> 00:22:04,400
it's...

394
00:22:16,160 --> 00:22:17,160
Wh-what?

395
00:22:19,010 --> 00:22:20,010
A secret.

396
00:22:20,820 --> 00:22:22,070
I'm not gonna

397
00:22:25,980 --> 00:22:26,980
tell you that easily.

398
00:22:29,020 --> 00:22:30,020
Good night.

399
00:22:32,050 --> 00:22:33,050
Yeah.

400
00:22:33,830 --> 00:22:34,830
Good night.

401
00:22:55,000 --> 00:22:57,400
(Next Episode)
(It's the final day of the school trip.)

402
00:22:57,460 --> 00:22:59,346
(My heart's racing seeing him in
that kimono...) Your hair is a mess.

403
00:22:59,370 --> 00:23:00,620
There. All better.

404
00:23:00,800 --> 00:23:02,643
(A new rival appears?!)
It really is you!

405
00:23:02,668 --> 00:23:03,668
You're here too?

406
00:23:04,180 --> 00:23:05,900
What is this, some kind of hottie festival?

407
00:23:06,240 --> 00:23:07,440
If you wouldn't mind...

408
00:23:08,160 --> 00:23:09,360
would you like to... with me?
